 <title>The Discouerie of Magic</title>
 <link>http://elf.org/the-discouerie-of-magic</link>
 <description>&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.boingboing.net/2009/11/12/a-peek-inside-a-17th.html&quot;&gt;Boing Boing&lt;/a&gt; linked to some articles about the original book of magic tricks, &lt;i&gt;Hocus Pocus Junior,&lt;/i&gt; (1634).  &lt;i&gt;Hocus Pocus Junior&lt;/i&gt; was actually a remix of parts of Reginald Scot&#039;s &lt;i&gt;The Discoverie of Witchcraft&lt;/i&gt; (1584), published 50 years earlier to debunk all sorts of magic.
&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;i&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.archive.org/details/discoverieofwitc00scot&quot;&gt;The Discouerie of Witchcraft&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt; is available in a beautifully scanned copy of an 1886 reprint.&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://elf.org/the-discouerie-of-magic&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
